1. The Ethereum Foundation Board of Directors announced the addition of new members;
2. The support rate of SOL's latest proposal SIMD-0228 reached 12.4%. If it is pledged, the income will shrink;
3. AC may launch a new project flyingtulip, which is positioned as a high-leverage contract exchange;
4. A whale accurately shorted BTC, with unrealized profits exceeding US$7.5 million;
5. Bitcoin spot ETF had a net outflow of US$799 million last week, and only Grayscale Bitcoin Mini Trust BTC achieved net inflow;
6. Ethereum spot ETF had a net outflow of US$120 million last week, and Grayscale Ethereum Mini Trust ETH had a net inflow of US$8.46 million, ranking first;
7. Robinhood agreed to pay about US$30 million to resolve the investigation by US regulators;
8. US Treasury Secretary Rooney denied the possibility of a recession;
9. A whale increased its long position and currently has a floating loss of US$14.39 million.
